&lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; is a 2005 short documentary film about canadian director hubert davis ' relationship to his father , former harlem &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; member mel davis . through interviews with his mother , his father 's wife , his half-brother , and mel davis himself , hubert davis explores why mel made the decisions that he did , and how that has affected his life . &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; was met with high critical acclaim and received an academy award for documentary short subject nomination . it also aired on pbs as part of its point of view series in 2005 .